The paper deals with the problem of estimating the degree of sparsity from compressive measurements, which is a common problem in signal processing and information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SP (Signal Processing) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the coherence of measurement matrices, which is a topic in linear algebra and optimization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely sub-category as well. The use of Khatri-Rao and Vandermonde matrices suggests that the paper may also fall under cs.MM (Mathematical Methods) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
